<div id="review_3689013282" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3689013282" />
    <a title="Pegboard" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/47722544-pegboard"><img alt="Pegboard" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1498516338p2/47722544.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3689013282?book_show_action=true">Dec 17, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pegboard" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pegboard" href="/user/show/47722544-pegboard">Pegboard</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3689013282" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5732434666831136341">The Taste of Despair by Darin C. Brown is the third book in his Master of Perceptions series. Hunter Miller is now fourteen, as is getting a better grip of his gift in perceiving other people&apos;s auras. His friend, Ian, has the ability of reading people by their body language. This helps Hunter understand the colors he sees coming off people and their significance. While only his grandfather knows about Hunter’s gift, it is hard to hide it from others close to him. This book covers many changes in</span>
  <span id="freeText5732434666831136341" style="display:none">The Taste of Despair by Darin C. Brown is the third book in his Master of Perceptions series. Hunter Miller is now fourteen, as is getting a better grip of his gift in perceiving other people's auras. His friend, Ian, has the ability of reading people by their body language. This helps Hunter understand the colors he sees coming off people and their significance. While only his grandfather knows about Hunter’s gift, it is hard to hide it from others close to him. This book covers many changes in Hunter’s life as he faces personal challenges at home and with his friends.<br /><br />Darin C. Brown has created a likeable superhero who struggles with autism and the unique challenges it presents. The Taste of Despair takes this teenager through many trials teenagers face, plus some. It immediately drew me to Hunter for his drive to understand those around him and his compassion for others. When he hits a valley in his life, it sends him into a void that takes days to weeks to recover from. Overall, this book has a fascinating plot and characters, but it also touches on the unique mental process of someone who is autistic. Though not all think the same, it would help to give a young person a healthy respect for those who have a distinct thinking pattern.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5732434666831136341" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


